  "text": "These results can be easily verified in the following graph of M ( ). 15 [CITATION_1] Note that throughout this paper, the graphs are used to illustrate the general trend rather than the exact shape of variables. For example, we know M ( ) always initially increases to a maximum, then decrease, and finally becomes a constant as shown in Figure 1 . But M ( ) may not be concave as in Figure 1 . The same applies to all other figures.",
